# Added 2026-04-20 — catch common secret filename patterns (three incidents in one session)
Anthropic-Key
**/Anthropic-Key
**/*-Key
**/*-Token
**/*-PAT
**/*-Secret

# Surgical secret-file patterns. Earlier broad pattern **/*[Kk]ey* swallowed
# legitimate code (keys.js, 002-provider-keys.sql, Phase_2.5_Key_Console/).
# Rule of thumb here: only match files that look LIKE secrets, not files
# ABOUT secrets.
#
# 1) No-extension files containing token-shaped words (typical of pasted-key
#    files saved by humans without thinking about extensions).
**/*-Key
**/*-Token
**/*-PAT
**/*-Secret
**/*-Credentials
**/Git-PAT*
**/Anthropic-Key*
**/Claude*Key*
**/*Open*Router*Key*
**/factory-master-key
# 2) Common "secrets file" basenames regardless of extension.
**/secrets.txt
**/credentials.txt
**/*.secret
